    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup for April 28th is headlined by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands the highest efficiency score of 76.47. Facing a favorable matchup against N. Martinez (4.59 xERA), **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is an auto-start, bolstered by his prime spot in the order and a massive SP skill advantage. **Bryson Stott** (72.10) and **Gleyber Torres** (67.46) also project as elite plays. **Gleyber Torres** is particularly intriguing; his 67.46 score is driven by a significant platoon advantage against the lefty P\u00e9rez and a strong historical BvP profile (+8%). Meanwhile, **Bryson Stott** benefits from a high-upside matchup against Mahle; although he faces a defensive headwind due to an elite opposing catcher, his raw skill differential keeps him well within the recommended starting range.\n\nEfficiency metrics emphasize park factors and platoon splits, with **Yainer Diaz** (61.21) and **Taylor Ward** (60.53) both receiving a 16% lift from their home park environments. **Jonathan Aranda** (63.16) and **Will Smith** (61.71) remain core offensive pillars, both benefiting from solid xERA matchups. The most difficult decision today involved the bench; **Luis Arraez** (44.59) was the closest to cracking the starting nine, but his sub-optimal matchup against the high-skill lefty Luzardo pushed his efficiency below the threshold of our current starters. We are prioritizing players like **Masyn Winn** (45.36) and **Tyler Freeman** (45.44) for their slightly better contextual fit, even as we remain mindful that **Tyler Freeman** is facing a stiff challenge from the elite arm of Burns (2.76 xERA).\n\nWe are tracking several volatility risks across the board. While **Daulton Varsho** (48.88) provides value, his score is suppressed by a negative platoon shift against Tolle, and we must monitor the status of **Jeremiah Jackson** (55.92) closely, as his position at the bottom of the order (-8%) limits his run production ceiling despite the favorable park environment. Managers should keep an eye on **Cal Raleigh** (49.56); despite an excellent xwOBA of 0.371, his efficiency is hampered by a difficult matchup against Ryan. We are holding **Matt Chapman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve, as their current projections against the challenging Luzardo do not justify displacing our high-scoring incumbents.",
